<% layout("../layouts/boilerplate.ejs") %>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/pages/responsible-hosting.css">

<div class="info-page">
    <div class="info-container">
        <div class="page-header">
            <i class="bi bi-house-check-fill"></i>
            <h1>Responsible Hosting</h1>
            <p>
                Hosting comes with responsibilities. Learn how to create a safe,
                welcoming, and compliant experience for your guests while being a
                positive member of your local community.
            </p>
        </div>

        <section class="info-section">
            <h2>
                <i class="bi bi-shield-check"></i>
                Prioritize Guest Safety
            </h2>
            <p>
                Ensure your property is clean, secure, and properly maintained.
                Provide working smoke detectors, fire extinguishers, emergency
                contacts, and clear safety instructions for guests.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="info-section">
            <h2>
                <i class="bi bi-building"></i>
                Follow Local Laws
            </h2>
            <p>
                Hosts are responsible for understanding and complying with local
                regulations, zoning laws, licensing requirements, tax obligations,
                and housing rules that apply to short-term rentals.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="info-section">
            <h2>
                <i class="bi bi-stars"></i>
                Provide Accurate Listings
            </h2>
            <p>
                Describe your property honestly. Include accurate photos,
                amenities, room details, and pricing information so guests know
                exactly what to expect before booking.
            </p>

            <div class="hosting-tip">
                <i class="bi bi-lightbulb-fill"></i>
                <span>
                    Accurate listings build trust and lead to better reviews.
                </span>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="info-section">
            <h2>
                <i class="bi bi-chat-left-text-fill"></i>
                Communicate Clearly
            </h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Respond to guest inquiries promptly.</li>
                <li>Provide clear check-in instructions.</li>
                <li>Inform guests about house rules.</li>
                <li>Be transparent about fees and policies.</li>
                <li>Address concerns professionally and respectfully.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="info-section">
            <h2>
                <i class="bi bi-people-fill"></i>
                Respect Your Community
            </h2>
            <p>
                Encourage guests to respect neighbors, avoid excessive noise,
                follow parking regulations, and maintain community standards
                during their stay.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="info-section">
            <h2>
                <i class="bi bi-house-heart-fill"></i>
                Maintain Property Standards
            </h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Keep rooms clean and well-maintained.</li>
                <li>Inspect safety equipment regularly.</li>
                <li>Repair issues promptly.</li>
                <li>Ensure advertised amenities are available.</li>
                <li>Provide a comfortable guest experience.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="info-section">
            <h2>
                <i class="bi bi-award-fill"></i>
                Build Trust Through Hospitality
            </h2>
            <p>
                Responsible hosting goes beyond providing accommodation. It
                involves creating memorable experiences, maintaining transparency,
                respecting guests, and contributing positively to the travel
                community.
            </p>
        </section>
    </div>
</div>